  urldate = {2023-03-02},
  abstract = {ONE OF THE DEALS THAT PAVED the way to enacting the Wilderness Act was an agreement between the Kennedy administration and House Interior Committee chair Wayne Aspinall on three other pieces of legislation. All became law on September 19, 1964, sixteen days after the Wilderness Act. The first launched a pet project of Aspinall's, the Public Land Law Review Commission (PLLRC), to study and recommend reforms in the nation's laws dealing with public lands (other than military lands and those in the national park system).{$^1$}  The second, the Classification and Multiple Use Act (CMUA), had been promoted by the administration.},
